The paper discusses the use of dropout for regularizing neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific problem being addressed is matrix factorization, which is a common task in both artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a fixed dropout rate, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and the optimization of the dropout rate based on the size of the factorization, which relates to signal processing (cs.SI).
